  "texts": [
    "The cost function C(v i, v i+1) incorporates factors such as distance, safety constraints, and environmental dynamics.",
    "Specifically, it is defined as:C(v i, v i+1) = w 1 • distance(v i, v i+1) + w 2 • safety_constraints(v i, v i+1) + w 3 • environmental_dynamics(v i, v i+1),where w 1, w 2, and w 3 are weights empirically derived through sensitivity analysis to balance these factors.",
    "6) Conflict Resolution Between Commands and Environmental Constraints:The EKG resolves conflicts between commands and environmental constraints using graph-based reasoning and prioritization.",
    "When a command is issued, the EKG validates it against the environment's current state, represented as nodes and edges.",
    "Conflicts occur when commands violate safety thresholds, spatial constraints, or dynamic conditions."
